==Chinese==
===Mandarin===
[[Pinyin]]: yī shān bù róng èr hŭ

===Etymology===
Literally: One mountain cannot have two tigers.

===Proverb===
'''[[一]][[山]][[不]][[容]][[二]][[虎]]''' ([[Simplified Chinese]])

# There can only be one alpha male.
# This town isn't big enough for the two of us.

